"the wheel is touched and moved. See settings above for adjustments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:123
msgid "22"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:123
msgid "Scratch Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid ""
"When this button is enabled, Smart Scratch mode will be active. In this "
"mode, the track's timeline continues (the lower half of the waveform in the "
"display will continue moving forward) when you use the platter to "
"\"scratch\" the track. When you release the platter, the track will resume "
"normal playback from where it would have been if you had never moved the "
"platter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + **Press:** enable or disable jog mode. In this mode, "
"touch the platter and move it to temporarily adjust the track's speed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid ""
"Press this button again to disable Smart Scratch and enable vinyl mode for "
"the platter. You can use the platter to \"scratch\" the track as you would "
"with a vinyl record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:126
msgid "23"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:126
msgid "Sync / Sync Off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid "Hold this button to activate or deactivate sync."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:127
msgid "24"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:127
msgid "Cue / Previous"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid ""
"When the Deck is paused, you can set a Temporary Cue Point by moving the "
"platter to place the playhead at the desired location and then pressing the "
"Cue Button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid ""
"During playback, you can press the Cue Button to return the track to this "
"Temporary Cue Point. (If you did not set a Temporary Cue Point, then it will"
" return to the beginning of the track.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid ""
"**Hold:** play the track from the Temporary Cue Point. Releasing the Cue "
"Button will return the track to the Temporary Cue Point and pause it. To "
"continue playback without returning to the Temporary Cue Point, press and "
"hold the Cue Button, then press and hold the Play Button, and then release "
"both buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid ":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + **Press:** return to the beginning of the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:131
msgid "25"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:131
msgid "Play/Pause"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid "Press this button to pause or resume playback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:0
msgid ""
":hwlabel:`SHIFT` + **Press:** \"stutter-play\" the track from the initial "
"cue point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixstream_pro.rst:133
msgid "26"
msgstr ""

